id: module-cognition-gate-promote-query-memory-rule
description: Cognition-gate should append retrieved real-world memory content on the second activation of an ongoing session.
modules = ["cognition-gate"]
prompt: Admit retrieved memory evidence only if it is load-bearing for the current situation.
context: The first activation admits the peer question into cognition. The second activation receives a production-format query-memory memo with the remembered world rule. The artifact must include a newly appended cognition-log entry from the second activation, not plain assistant text.

limits {
  max-llm-calls = 8
}

@ steps[] {
  description: Initial sensory/question context becomes the current cognition surface.

  @ memos[] {
    module: sensory
    content: Pibi is at the edge of a bright, clear stream, lowering its head toward the water. Pibi asked, "This stream looks fresh -- is it okay to drink here?"
  }
}

@ steps[] {
  description: Retrieved world rule arrives after the first cognition entry.

  @ memos[] {
    module: query-memory
    content = ```
Query intent:
- Find stable memory that clarifies this cognition-log context: Pibi is at the edge of a bright, clear stream, lowering its head toward the water. Pibi asked, "This stream looks fresh -- is it okay to drink here?"

Search queries:
- Pibi is at the edge of a bright, clear stream, lowering its head toward the water. Pibi asked, "This stream looks fresh -- is it okay to drink here?"

Retrieved memory evidence:
<one-year-ago occurred-at="2025-05-09T15:00:00Z">
In this valley, bright clear-looking streams are tainted with stinging minerals; they hurt the mouth and stomach. The cloudy slow streams that come from the moss area are the safe ones to drink.
</one-year-ago>
```
  }
}

@ checks[] {
  $variant: trace-tool-call
  name: uses-promote-to-cognition-tool
  must-pass = true
  tool-name: promote_to_cognition
}

@ checks[] {
  $variant: json-pointer-contains
  name: cognition-contains-stinging-minerals-rule
  must-pass = true
  pointer: /observations/agent/cognition_logs
  contains: stinging minerals
}

@ checks[] {
  $variant: artifact-text-contains
  name: promotes-memory-subject
  must-pass = true
  contains: stream
}

@ checks[] {
  $variant: rubric
  name: promotes-load-bearing-inner-attention
  must-pass = true
  pass-score = 0.85
  judge-inputs = ["output", "memo-contents", "cognition-entries"]
  rubric = ```
  Pass if the artifact brings the remembered valley stream rule into cognition because it is relevant to Pibi's current question, while preserving the requester/topic relationship enough for downstream modules to act: Pibi is asking about the bright stream, and the bright-clear-stream / stinging-minerals rule matters now.
  The cognition entry may be an inner-attention note rather than an outward utterance; it does not need to be phrased as speech.
  Fail if it drops the requester or the operative stinging-minerals / safe-cloudy-moss-streams detail, treats the remembered rule as irrelevant, turns the entry into generic "retrieve or process this later" work, only repeats the seeded fact that the stream looks fresh, returns the cognition as plain assistant text without a promote_to_cognition tool call, or exposes mechanical implementation details such as module names, search terms, memo plumbing, prompts, rubrics, or evals.
  ```

  @ criteria[] {
    name: preserves-requester-and-topic
    weight = 1
    pass-score = 0.85
    description: The cognition entry keeps Pibi as the requester and the bright stream as the operative topic.
  }

  @ criteria[] {
    name: admits-tainted-stream-rule
    weight = 3
    pass-score = 0.9
    description: The cognition entry must admit the retrieved world rule that bright clear streams in this valley are tainted with stinging minerals, hurt the mouth/stomach, or that cloudy moss-area streams are the safe alternative. Score 0.0 if the entry only repeats Pibi's question or only says the water looks fresh.
  }

  @ criteria[] {
    name: no-internal-detail-leak
    weight = 1
    pass-score = 0.95
    description: The cognition entry does not expose internal implementation details such as module names, memo plumbing, prompts, rubrics, or hidden evaluation mechanics.
  }
}
